iety of its services and amenities, United recently launched extensive upgrade and expansion programs. United is now the only U.S. airline to offer seats that recline to a 180-degree flat position and personal on-demand entertainment systems on first class and business class international long-haul flights from all three New York airports. It also provides live television viewing on 200 of its airplanes.<br />\n    <br />\n    The company maintains more than 50 United Clubs at 38 airports around the world, featuring complimentary cocktails, snacks and beverages, business services and personal workstations.</p>\n\n    <h2>First Class In The Air</h2>\n\n    <p>In addition to full-flat beds and personal entertainment systems, domestic first class passengers enjoy adjustable headrests, an iPod adapter, a power outlet, over-sized leather seats and expedited check-in, boarding and security queues.<br />\n    <br />\n    Additional services for international first class flights include premium personal care kits, comfortable duvets and pillows, exclusive bed turn-down service, lumbar support and back stimulation with United&#39;s BackCycler&reg; motion system and a customized dining experience.</p>\n\n    <h2>Business Class In The Air &amp; Cheap Business Class</h2>\n\n    <p>In addition to more spacious seating, multi-course meals and a variety of entertainment options, business class passengers enjoy priority security screening. Aboard United BusinessFirst&reg; international flights, <strong>business travelers</strong> are treated to complimentary toiletry kits, individual seat controls for lie-flat seats and snuggle-worthy duvets and pillows. Ergonomic tray tables, USB ports and a power outlet provide comfortable in-air work spaces.</p>\n\n    <div><br />\n    United Airlines and FlyFirst.com<br />\n    United&#39;s breadth of travel connections, choice of itineraries and frequently upgraded first and business class services provide the highest <strong>luxury</strong> and flexibility for all of its passengers. FlyFirst.com&#39;s tremendously <strong>reduced first class tickets</strong> and <strong>last minute</strong> <strong>business class deals</strong> ensure that you receive the ultimate in service for less than half of United&#39;s published fares.</div>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(4, 'First Class Tickets cheap, Business Class Air, Last Minute First Class Tickets', 'Cheap Business Class Flights, First Class Airline, Last Minute Business Class Deals, Cheap Fare , Cheap Tickets ', 'Delta', 'Business-First-Class-Cheap-Delta', 'First Class Tickets & Discounted Business Class Fare , Save Thousands on Delta, Book with FlyFirst', 'FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights On Delta, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares on Delta. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.\n', '<h4><strong>FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights on Delta, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares on Delta. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.</strong></h4>\n\n    <p>Relish the phenomenal savings FlyFirst.com provides on Delta Air Lines&#39; award-winning first class fares and business class flights. As a luxury traveler, you&#39;ll be treated to complimentary world-class dining, exclusive airport lounges and pampering services while paying up to 70 percent less than your fellow passengers.</p>\n\n    <h2>About Delta Air Lines</h2>\n\n    <h4><strong>Cheap Business &amp; First Class Flights on Delta. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Last Minute Business Class Tickets. Affordable Price for Business Class Seats. Call Us Now to Book &amp; Save up to 70%</strong></h4>\n\n    <p>Delta delivers more than 160 million passengers a year to 318 destinations across 59 countries. Based in Atlanta, Ga., Delta maintains one of the largest aircraft fleets in the world with 722 airplanes. Dedicated to improving its fleet and customer experiences, Delta is conducting a $3 billion improvement plan. Currently, the airline operates the world&#39;s largest fleet of wireless Internet-equipped aircraft. Delta earned more than 30 airline industry awards for its services and received the Secretary of Defense Freedom Award for supporting its National Guard and reserve employees. The company operates with 80,000 employees around the world.</p>\n\n    <h2>Delta At The Airport</h2>\n\n    <p>First class and international business class passengers receive complimentary access to Delta&#39;s welcoming Sky Club airport lounges. There, travelers delight in a wide variety of complimentary snacks, beverages and cocktails as well as refreshing showers, comfortable armchairs and a variety of other services.</p>\n\n    <h2>Cheap First Class, Affordable Fares</h2>\n\n    <p>Delta&#39;s first class is available on all domestic and <strong>international flights</strong>, offering in-flight wireless high-speed Internet, power outlets, USB ports, live satellite television, hundreds of movies and thousands of music selections. Passengers on lengthy flights dine on entrees created by Delta&#39;s team of celebrity chefs; on shorter flights, passengers enjoy a variety of snacks and beverages. First class passengers appreciate expedited check-in, security and boarding queues that eliminate unnecessary wait times.</p>\n\n    <h2>Discounted Business Class</h2>\n\n    <p>Delta Elite is Delta&#39;s international business class also available on transcontinental routes between New York and San Francisco or Los Angeles. Delta Elite travelers savor extensive entertainment options, a delectable wine menu created by a master sommelier and Westin Heavenly&reg; bedding of large, luscious comforters and full-size down-alternative pillows. Transcontinental passengers savor cuisine designed by famed chef Michael Chiarello, while intercontinental travelers dine on seasonal, five-course meals created by renowned chefs. Seat types depend on the type of aircraft involved, but range in