(1, 'Cheap Buisiness Class Flights to Seoul, Korea', 'Cheap Buisiness Class Flights to Seoul, Korea', 'Cheap Buisiness Class Flights to Seoul, Korea, Save Thousands on First Class Tickets ', 'Business-Class-First-Cheap-Seoul', '2013-05-22 00:00:00', 'FlyFirst Reveals Discounts on Business Class Fares to South Korea&#160;\n    FlyFirst, the business class and first class travel experts, announced today that it is offering dramatically discounted business class air Fares to Korea&#160;Travelers using the expert services of FlyFirst can take advantage of fare discounts of up to 60 percent off regular ticket prices to the bustling finance and tourist hub of Seoul and other South Korean destinations.\n', '<p>FlyFirst Reveals Discounts on Business Class Fares to South Korea&#160;<br />\n    FlyFirst, the business class and first class travel experts, announced today that it is offering dramatically discounted business class air Fares to Korea&#160;Travelers using the expert services of FlyFirst can take advantage of fare discounts of up to 60 percent off regular ticket prices to the bustling finance and tourist hub of Seoul and other South Korean destinations.</p>\n\n    <p>&#8220;Flights from the U.S. to South Korea can range from nearly 12 hours to a little more than 14 hours, so we are delighted to be able to offer our customers affordable fares in the more comfortable business class cabins,&#8221; says Julia Graft, FlyFirst PR manager. &#8220;Whether traveling for business or pleasure, alone or with colleagues or family, business class seating is more spacious and better suited to lengthy and overnight flights.&#8221; Plus,Business Class Ttavelers&#160;can avail themselves of all the other perks of business class, such as higher-end meal service, large work space areas, greater entertainment options and access to service-oriented airport lounges. &#8220;To be able to offer all those business class amenities at tremendously discounted rates is what FlyFirst is all about,&#8221; Graft notes.</p>\n\n    <p>Its drastically reduced business air fares to South Korea and other international destinations are a result of FlyFirst network of partnerships with leading travel clearinghouses and companies. Those relationships enable FlyFirst to provide hundreds of discounted business class fares on the world&#39;s best airlines and reduced rates on ground transportation and lodging. Even last minute flights, complicated multi-city itineraries and difficult connections can be accommodated by FlyFirst&#8217; travel experts. The ultimate goal is to provide a seamless travel experience that is hassle-free for all customers, whether they are traveling on holiday or for an important business trip.</p>\n\n    <p>&#8220;These deeply reduced fares are especially helpful since Seoul is rapidly becoming a leading travel destination for professionals and vacationers,&#8221; Graft says. Its metropolitan economy ranks fourth in the world and is known for its vast technology industry that includes Samsung and LG. On top of its extensive economic draw for global businesses, Seoul is increasingly popular with pleasure travelers. In 2012, the dynamic metropolis accommodated more than 10 million international travelers. Many of those visitors enjoy the city&#39;s abundant attractions, including Lotte World, the largest indoor theme park in the world and Moonlight Rainbow Fountain, the largest bridge fountain on earth. &#8220;There is so much to experience in Seoul, and we are proud to be able to offer such profoundly discounted business class fares to South Korea&#39;s most popular destinations,&#8221; says Graft.</p>\n\n    <p>To book a discounted business class ticket to South Korea, call the FlyFirst travel experts at (888) 347-7817 or online at FlyFirst.com.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2, 'Discounted Business Class, Bests Deals, Save on First Class, Cheap Business', 'Cheap Business Class to Europe, Last Minute First Class, Discounted Fares, Cheap Flights.', 'Cheap Business Class, FlyFirst Offers First Class Service Fit for an Action Movie Star', 'Cheap-First-Class-Tickets', '2013-05-22 00:00:00', 'Action movie star and famed martial artist Jean-Claude Van Damme took advantage of FlyFirst&#39;s outstanding deals and personalized service to book his recent first class flight to Singapore. Best known for his roles in the movies&#160;Bloodsport,&#160;Street Fighter&#160;and&#160;Timecop, Van Damme received FlyFirst&#39;s unparalleled personalized service and luxury flight fares at far below published rates. With Van Damme on board, FlyFirst again shows that its legendary discounts and customer service are fit for an action hero.\n', '<p><strong>FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights to Asia, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares to Europe. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.</strong></p>\n\n    <div id="textpreview">Action movie star and famed martial artist Jean-Claude Van Damme took advantage of FlyFirst&#39;s outstanding deals and personalized service to book his recent first class flight to Singapore. Best known for his roles in the movies&#160;<em>Bloodsport</em>,&#160;<em>Street Fighter</em>&#160;and&#160;<em>Timecop</em>, Van Damme received Fly First&#39;s unparalleled personalized service and luxury flight fares at far below published rates. With Van Damme on board, Fly First again shows that its legendary discounts and customer service are fit for an action hero.<br />\n    <br />\n    Van Damme is not the only celebrity to use FlyFirst for premium travel planning. The travel professionals at Fly First have supplied discounts on luxury flights for celebrities, executives and savvy travelers for more than nine years. Often, these industry titans depend on FlyFirst to coordinate sudden, complicated and uncertain travel itineraries at the best possible prices and with the utmost attention to detail. Unexpected delays, sudden travel changes and unpredictable issues can cost these VIPs millions of dollars. They rely on FlyFirst to ensure that all travel contingencies are resolved quickly.<br />\n    <br />\n    Known for our simplified booking process, prospective customers simply complete our online form by listing preferred travel dates, choice of departure and arrival cities, cabin type and contact information. Immediately, Fly First goes to work unearthing the very best possible first class and business class deals available. Our travel professionals then offer clients several travel and pricing options and schedule the itinerary accordingly.<br />\n    <br />\n    From the time Fly First receives a travel request to the time the customer arrives home, our travel professionals remain committed to smoothing the way for a flawless travel experience. Last minute itinerary changes and emergencies are no problem for FlyFirst experts who continue to assist customers throughout their travels. Customers never travel alone when they book with Fly First.<br />\n    <br />\n    On top of industry-leading expertise and service, FlyFirst offers discounts for as much as 70 percent off published luxury airfare rates. Sometimes, our experts can find first class and business class fares that are as affordable as cheap coach airfares. Currently, Fly First offers business class flights to Singapore for as little as $3,370 and first class flights to London for $3,740.<br />\n    <br />\n    Fly First maintains strong relationships with all of the major air carriers and a variety of travel companies. These partnerships give FlyFirst customers access to deals on all the major international airlines, including British Airways, Cathay Pacific, Emirates, United, Lufthansa and Virgin Atlantic. These airlines receive stellar marks for first class cabin design, high-end cuisine, comfortable seating and amenity-filled first and business class airport lounges.<br />\n    <br />\n    These unrivaled services provided by Fly First have been featured in national broadcasts including &#160;Yahoo, San Francisco Chronicle and others. FlyFirst is a member of the American Society of Travel Agents, the Better Business Bureau and the National Association of Career Travel Agents.&#160;<br />\n    <br />\n    For more information about Fly First, visit www.FlyFirst.com or call (888) 347-7817.</div>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3, 'Discounted Fares on Business and First Class to Asia', 'Discounted Fares on Business and First Class to Asia', 'Discounted Fares on Business and First Class to Asia, Last Minute Flights', 'Cheap-Business-Class-to-Asia', '2013-05-22 00:00:00', 'FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights to Asia, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares to Asia. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.\n', '<p><strong>Cheap Business &amp; First Class Flights to Asia. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Last Minute Business Class Tickets. Affordable Price for Business Class Seats. Call Us Now to Book &amp; Save up to 70%</strong></p>\n\n    <p>First class flights to Asia are now more attainable than ever with FlyFirst newly released discounts of up to 70 percent off regular fares. Specializing in affordable business class and first class travel, FlyFirst announced the new first class Asia Dissounts today, just in time for the busy spring and summer travel seasons. First class flights to busy Asian destinations such as Hong Kong, Seoul and Singapore start at just $4,685, and include all the usual luxurious first class services and amenities.</p>\n\n    <p>&quot;Ordinarily, some of these first class tickets to vibrant Asian destinations such as Hong Kong and Singapore could cost more than $15, 000,&quot; notes Julia Graft, PR manager for FlyFirst. &quot;Most Asian markets are booming, and FlyFirst is proud to be able to offer such affordable first class fares for business travelers and vacationers. These unbelievable low fares give growing global businesses and families on holiday a chance to experience the&#160;<a href="http://www.iflyfirstclass.com/" target="_blank" title="last minute business class fares">luxurious first class</a>&#160;cabin accommodations without breaking any budgets.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>FlyFirst offers hundreds of these discounted fares to most major Asian destinations. The 70-percent savings are available on many last minute flights, multi-city itineraries and for flights arranged well in advance of the travel dates. Many of the discounted first class seats are aboard the world&#39;s most highly recognized first class airlines.</p>\n\n    <p>A first class ticket is an entree to a world of unparalleled luxury and service. Exquisite dining featuring meals designed by world-renowned chefs, spacious private seating arrangements, bed turn-down services and free-flowing champagne are the hallmarks of first class airline service. Many of the airlines&#39; first class airport lounges offer complimentary spa treatments, dining, beverage service, varied entertainment and ample work spaces to start the travel experience on the right note. Some airlines even offer a separate airport terminal and customs desks for first class passengers.</p>\n\n    <p>&quot;We are confident that travelers will enjoy the customized first-class service offered by our airline partners, and we are delighted to be able to offer that sumptuous luxury travel up to 70% off&#160;rack prices,&quot; Graft says. &quot;Whether traveling on vacation or in pursuit of business expansion, these first class rates are unrivaled.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>To book a first class seat to Asia at up to 70 percent off, call the travel experts at FlyFirst at (888) 347-7817</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(4, 'Cheap Business Class to London', 'Cheap Business Class to London', 'Cheap Business Class to London, Discounted First Class & Last Minute Flight Deals ', 'Last-Minute-Business-Deals-to-London', '2013-05-23 10:38:43', 'Traveling first class or business class to London is more affordable than ever with new, cheaper fares announced by the travel experts at FlyFirst. Once known as &ldquo;The Big Smoke,&rdquo; London boasts a thriving financial center, a vibrant theater and arts scene and some of the most famous historical sites in Westren Europe. Flying from the United States to London in comfort and style is budget-friendly with FlyFirst&#39; newly released air fares. Business class fares begin at just $2,684, and white-glove first class fares start at only $3,589.\n', '<p>Traveling first class or business class to London is more affordable than ever with new, cheaper fares announced by the travel experts at FlyFirst. Once known as &#8220;The Big Smoke,&#8221; London boasts a thriving financial center, a vibrant theater and arts scene and some of the most famous historical sites in Westren Europe. Flying from the United States to London in comfort and style is budget-friendly with FlyFirst&#39; newly released air fares. Business class fares begin at just $2,684, and white-glove first class fares start at only $3,589.</p>\n\n    <p>&#8220;These outstanding rates are perfect for professionals who want to bring family along on business trips to London or simply for family pleasure vacations,&#8221; says Julia Graft, PR manager for FlyFirst. &#8220;Business class and first class seats are roomier and more luxurious than coach seats, so this is a great and affordable way for adults and kids to travel on the long flight between the U.S. and London.&#8221;</p>\n\n    <p>With so much to see and experience in London, it&#39;s no wonder the city welcomes more than 14 million visitors each year. History lovers can spend days exploring the varied sites in and around London, including Westminster Abbey, the Tower of London and Tower Bridge, Trafalgar Square, the Parliament Building with its infamous Big Ben bell and St. Paul&#39;s Cathedral.</p>\n\n    <p>Theater buffs and style mavens will delight in London&#39;s West End district where they can take in a top-rated musical such as Les Miserables or A Chorus Line, enjoy a few nightclubs or explore the many shops and boutiques along the mile-long Oxford Street. London proclaims itself the shopping capital of the world, featuring more than 26,000 stores and the headquarters of noted designers like Stella McCartney, Jimmy Choo and Manolo Blahnik.</p>\n\n    <p>London is a haven for art afficionados and &#8220;foodies&#8221; as well. World-famous modern art museum Tate Modern is one of London&#39;s most iconic tourist stops, as are the Victoria and Albert Museum and the National Gallery. The city&#39;s 6,000 restaurants offer every type of cuisine imaginable, including more than 50 Michelin Star restaurants.</p>\n\n    <p>For those who just want to roam the historic city, there are plenty of other sites to visit, including the London Eye, sporting events at Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park, Covent Garden, Picadilly Circus, Hyde Park and the Royal Botanic Gardens.</p>\n\n    <p>&#8220;London offers a wealth of business opportunity and cultural exploration, and&#160;FlyFirst&#160;makes it attainable with its inexpensive business class and first class air fares,&#8221; Graft says. For information about these deeply discounted business class and first class flights to London, call the travel experts at FlyFirst or visit them online at FlyFirst.com.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(5, 'FlyFirst Unveils Discounts on First Class Travel to Asia at Up to 70% OFF', 'FlyFirst Unveils Discounts on First Class Travel to Asia at Up to 70% OFF', 'FlyFirst Unveils Discounts on First Class Travel to Asia at Up to 70% OFF', 'First-Class-Cheap-to-Asia', '2013-05-26 12:04:10', 'First class flights to Asia are now more attainable than ever with FlyFirst newly released discounts of up to 70 percent off regular fares. Specializing in affordable business class and first class travel, FlyFirst announced the new first class&#160;Asia Discounts Today, just in time for the busy spring and summer travel seasons. First class flights to busy Asian destinations such as Hong Kong, Seoul and Singapore start at just $4,685, and include all the usual luxurious first class services and amenities.\n', '<h2>FlyFirst Unveils Discounts on First Class Travel to Asia at Up to 70% OFF</h2>\n\n    <p>First class flights to Asia are now more attainable than ever with FlyFirst newly released discounts of up to 70 percent off regular fares. Specializing in affordable business class and first class travel, FlyFirst announced the new first class&#160;<a href="http://www.iflyfirstclass.com/" target="_blank" title="cheap last minute business class">A</a>sia Discounts Today, just in time for the busy spring and summer travel seasons. First class flights to busy Asian destinations such as Hong Kong, Seoul and Singapore start at just $4,685, and include all the usual luxurious first class services and amenities.</p>\n\n    <p>&quot;Ordinarily, some of these first class tickets to vibrant Asian destinations such as Hong Kong and Singapore could cost more than $15, 000,&quot; notes Julia Graft, PR manager for FlyFirst. &quot;Most Asian markets are booming, and FlyFirst is proud to be able to offer such affordable first class fares for business travelers and vacationers. These unbelievable low fares give growing global businesses and families on holiday a chance to experience the luxury first class&#160;cabin accommodations without breaking any budgets.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>FlyFirst offers hundreds of these discounted fares to most major Asian destinations. The 70-percent savings are available on many last minute flights, multi-city itineraries and for flights arranged well in advance of the travel dates. Many of the discounted first class seats are aboard the world&#39;s most highly recognized first class airlines.</p>\n\n    <p>A first class ticket is an entree to a world of unparalleled luxury and service. Exquisite dining featuring meals designed by world-renowned chefs, spacious private seating arrangements, bed turn-down services and free-flowing champagne are the hallmarks of first class airline service. Many of the airlines&#39; first class airport lounges offer complimentary spa treatments, dining, beverage service, varied entertainment and ample work spaces to start the travel experience on the right note. Some airlines even offer a separate airport terminal and customs desks for first class passengers.</p>\n\n    <p>&quot;We are confident that travelers will enjoy the customized first-class service offered by our airline partners, and we are delighted to be able to offer that sumptuous&#160;<a href="http://www.iflyfirstclass.com/" target="_blank" title="cheap business class flight">L</a>uxury at u to 70% OFF&#160;rack prices,&quot; Graft says. &quot;Whether traveling on vacation or in pursuit of business expansion, these first class rates are unrivaled.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>To book a first class seat to Asia at up to 70 percent off, call the travel experts at FlyFirst at (888) 347-7817</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(6, ' FlyFirst Announces Deeply Discounted Business Class Fares to Europe', ' FlyFirst Announces Deeply Discounted Business Class Fares to Europe', ' FlyFirst Announces Deeply Discounted Business Class Fares to Europe', 'Business-First-Class-Europe', '2013-05-27 10:19:16', 'Business class and first class travel expert, FlyFirst announces its latest discounted business class fares to Australia on some of the world&#39;s most reputable and high-end airlines. Travel in business class comfort and style&#160;Europe&#160;from Australia. for as little as $3,894, round trip, and from to any other international destination with discounts as great as 60%\n', '<p>Business class and first class travel expert, FlyFirst announces its latest discounted business class fares to Australia on some of the world&#39;s most reputable and high-end airlines. Travel in business class comfort and style&#160;Europe&#160;from Australia. for as little as $3,894, round trip, and from to any other international destination with discounts as great as 60%. &quot;Most business class flights from the U.S. to Australia would cost at least twice that amount,&quot; notes Julia Graft, FF PR Manager. &quot;And since Australia is a terrific access point for popular Asian destinations, FF also is offering remarkable business class fares between Australia and other popular international locations.</p>\n\n    <p>&#160;</p>\n\n    <p><span style="font-size:20px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><span style="color:#b99d5b;">The special savings are valid on the following travel options:&#160;</span></span></span></p>\n\n    <p>&#160;</p>\n\n    <ul>\n    <li>\n    <p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Last Minute Fares on all major airlines&#160;</span></span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n    <p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Business and First Class Tickets to Asia&#160;</span></span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n    <p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Business and First Class Tickets To Europe&#160;</span></span></p>\n    </li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <p>&#160;</p>\n\n    <p>FlyFirst&#160; works hand-in-hand with airline wholesalers and travel companies to provide travelers the very best business class fares on the world&#39;s most highly rated airlines. Whether travelers are looking for last minute flights, complicated itineraries to multiple cities or other travel accommodations and transport, the experts at FF find and negotiate the best rates available. Because FF maintains long-standing relationships with its travel partners, it has access to deals not available to the general public and shares those tremendous savings with its customers. Best of all, in addition to its discounted fares, FF is known for its stellar customer service providing seamless, hassle-free travel experiences.</p>\n\n    <p>Lengthy international flights can be wearisome, so traveling in the comfort of business class makes sense. Having the space to work and sleep on a long, 14-hour flight from Los Angeles to Sydney can make the trip more enjoyable and productive. &#8220;Business class seats&#160;&#160;are wider and plusher, and often offer private video monitors, extra work space and other professional amenities,&#8221; Graft says. Many major airlines&#39; business class seats recline to a full-flat position so that travelers can sleep on long-haul or overnight flights. Business class travelers also receive more personalized service, special meals created by world-renowned chefs and access to exclusive airport lounges and other custom services.</p>\n\n    <p>Whether traveling to Australia for business or pleasure, business class accommodations can help travelers arrive in Oz rested, relaxed and ready to experience all that the country has to offer. Australia&#39;s two largest cities, Sydney and Melbourne, are not to be missed. Melbourne is home to a variety of art and cultural museums, sporting events and business districts. Sydney, known for its iconic waterfront Opera House, gives visitors a chance to make a breathtaking climb on the famous Harbour Bridge or enjoy the sand and surf on Bondi Beach. FlyFirst can coordinate further travel to Australia&#39;s other vibrant cities, such as the West Coast&#39;s Perth and the north&#39;s Darwin, all at unbeatable prices.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(7, 'FlyFirst Announces Top Tips for Cheap Business Class Flights', 'FlyFirst Announces Top Tips for Cheap Business Class Flights', 'FlyFirst Announces Top Tips for Cheap Business Class Flights', 'Cheap-Business-Class-Tickets', '2013-05-28 21:36:49', 'Today&#39;s global marketplace compels professionals to travel the world seeking access to new markets and working 24 hours a day, seven days a week in the process. The advent of business class air travel mirrors the growth of the global economy, creating a level of travel that offers far greater comfort and service than economy class. While not as expensive as first class,&#160;business class air fares can still be a bit pricey.\n', '<p><strong>FlyFirst Announces Top Tips for Cheap Business Class Flights</strong></p>\n\n    <p>Today&#39;s global marketplace compels professionals to travel the world seeking access to new markets and working 24 hours a day, seven days a week in the process. The advent of business class air travel mirrors the growth of the global economy, creating a level of travel that offers far greater comfort and service than economy class. While not as expensive as&#160;<a href="http://www.iflyfirstclass.com/" target="_blank" title="cheap business class to asia">f</a>irst class, business class air fares can still be a bit pricey.</p>\n\n    <p>The business and first class travel experts at FlyFirst(FF) want business and pleasure travelers to know that, with a little ingenuity and planning, business class fares are within reach for a variety of budgets. Here are a few of their tips for getting the best deals on business class travel:</p>\n\n    <p>Book in advance. The on-demand pricing structure of many airlines means that the earlier seats are booked, the better the pricing. Booking airfares one to two months ahead of time can translate to savings of up to 60 percent on many airlines. Now is a perfect time to start searching for, and booking, business class flights for late spring and early summer.</p>\n\n    <p>Be flexible. Just as with coach airfare, travelers willing to fly overnight, very early in the morning or on quieter days will realize the best savings. The benefits of business class are even more apparent on those red-eye flights, since travelers have more travel room and seats that are more suitable for sleeping.</p>\n\n    <p>Travel off-season. For business class, off-season is summertime when business slows down a bit to accommodate summer vacations and holidays. &quot;Particularly in Europe, where August is the sacred holiday month, business class capacity is often wide open in summer,&quot; advises Julia Graft, PR manager for FF. &quot;The abundance of seats makes summer a great time to travel via business class, especially if the travel is for a pleasure vacation.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>Take advantage of unsold seats.Business Class&#160;seats are very infrequently sold out, and those unsold seats often can be purchased at discounted prices, called Y-Up fares. Travelers can call the airlines or an airline booking service and ask for available Y-Up fares. These discounts are especially helpful if travel arrangements are being planned in less than 30 days.</p>\n\n    <p>Use frequent flier miles. Often, business class travel is less expensive when using frequent flier miles to supplement an unrestricted coach fare. Travelers can purchase an unrestricted ticket in economy/coach class, then call the airline to ask for an upgrade using mile credits obtained through rewards programs or credit card programs. Before committing to this method, however, travelers should check out the other options to determine the best pricing available.</p>\n\n    <p>Use a discount travel booking service. Travel experts&#160;like those at FF have years of experience in negotiating and unearthing the very best deals on business class travel. Using such a service can save travelers loads of time and money and pave the way for a hassle-free travel experience.</p>\n\n    <p>Whether travelers are flying across the world for business or across a continent for a family vacation, business class can offer the perfect combination of comfort and affordability. &quot;Using these FlyFirst tips, we are certain travelers can find reasonably priced business class airfares to suit their individual budgets,&quot; Graft concludes.</p>\n\n    <p>&#160;</p>\n\n    <p>&#160;</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(8, 'Famous Consumer Advocate Kevin Trudeau Uses FlyFirst for His Personal and Business Travel Needs', 'Famous Consumer Advocate Kevin Trudeau Uses FlyFirst for His Personal and Business Travel Needs', 'Famous Consumer Advocate Kevin Trudeau Uses FlyFirst for His Personal and Business Travel Needs', 'Firs-Class-Trips-Discount', '2013-05-29 06:08:17', 'The list of celebrities and stars using FlyFirst&#39;s deeply discounted luxury flight services just grew a little longer. Famous consumer nutrition and health advocate Kevin Trudeau recently booked a stellar first class flight deal with FlyFirst.com. With his travel reservation, Trudeau receives the high quality service and dramatically slashed first class fares that define FlyFirst.com.\n', '<p>The list of celebrities and stars using FlyFirst&#39;s deeply discounted luxury flight services just grew a little longer. Consumer nutrition and health advocate Kevin Trudeau recently booked a stellar first class flight deal with FlyFirst.com. With his travel reservation, Trudeau receives the high quality service and dramatically slashed first class fares that define FlyFirst.com.<br />\n    <br />\n    Radio show host and author Trudeau devotes much of his energy to consumer advocacy, so it&#39;s fitting that he chooses to save as much as 70 percent on premium air travel with FlyFirst.com. Trudeau, along with many other celebrities such as actor and martial artist Jean-Claude Van Damme, corporate executives, business professionals and experienced travelers count on FlyFirst.com to provide a flawless travel experience. Even better, they appreciate access to the same luxurious services and amenities as full-price customers while paying a fraction of the fare.<br />\n    <br />\n    FlyFirst provides customers with the complete confidence that they are receiving the very best available first class deals, business class fares and personalized service. Our travel experts are well-versed in all elements of travel planning, and they call on FlyFirst&#39;s extensive network of travel partners to provide unmatched discounts.<br />\n    <br />\n    The outstanding savings available through FlyFirst.com are valid for a variety of travel needs, including last minute first class flights, one-way trips, multi-city destinations, last minute business class tickets and open-ended return flights.<br />\n    <br />\n    Step-by-step, FlyFirst travel professionals remain dedicated to each customer&#39;s travel needs. There&#39;s never any need to worry about needing sudden mid-trip itinerary changes since FlyFirst&#39;s experts are available to smooth any and all unexpected changes, roadblocks and travel emergencies.<br />\n    <br />\n    We partner with all of the best international and domestic airlines to provide FlyFirst.com customers with access to top-rated air carriers. Our travel professionals are knowledgeable about all of the best airlines, international airports and airport lounges so that they can guide FlyFirst customers in selecting the itinerary that best suits their travel needs. Lufthansa, Cathay Pacific, British Airways, Delta, Virgin Atlantic and Emirates are just a few of the air carriers used by FlyFirst.com.<br />\n    <br />\n    FlyFirst&#39;s high-quality service and savings continue to receive nationwide attention in broadcasts around the country, Yahoo, San FRancisco Chronicle, Los Angeles Sun and many more. The company is known for its simplified international and domestic flight online request form. Travelers merely provide their contact information, preferred dates of travel, selected departure and destination cities and chosen class of travel. FlyFirst travel agents immediately scour their vast resources to find the best prices, and they then offer prospective travelers several itinerary options and airport suggestions. The overarching goal of FlyFirst.com is to provide customers with an impeccable travel experience from start to finish.<br />\n    <br />\n    FlyFirst.com is a member of the Better Business Bureau, the National Association of Career Travel Agents and the American Society of Travel Agents.<br />\n    <br />\n    For more information about FlyFirst.com and its broad range of discount luxury travel services, call (888) 347-7817 or visit the company online at FlyFirst.com.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9, 'FlyFirst Announces 10 Busiest Airports in the World,  cheap business class travel deals, cheap first class deals travel, cheap flights travel deals, Business travel, First Class Travel, cheap discounted business class travel ', 'FlyFirst Announces 10 Busiest Airports in the World Affordable Business Class , affordable first Class tickets, save money on business class airfare, save money on First Class Tickets', 'FlyFirst Announces 10 Busiest Airports in the World', 'Discount-Business-Class', '2013-06-02 16:52:47', 'More than 5.4 billion people traveled by air in 2011, an increase of 5.3 percent, and all indications point to a similarly steady growth in 2012. To help air passengers pinpoint the best airport for their own upcoming travels, the business class and first class&#160;travel experts at FlyFirst discuss the 2012&#39;s 10 Busiest Airports in the World, based on preliminary statistics compiled by the Airports Council International.\n', '<p>&#160;</p>\n\n    <p>More than 5.4 billion people traveled by air in 2011, an increase of 5.3 percent, and all indications point to a similarly steady growth in 2012. To help air passengers pinpoint the best airport for their own upcoming travels, the business class and first class&#160;travel experts at FlyFirst discuss the 2012&#39;s 10 Busiest Airports in the World, based on preliminary statistics compiled by the Airports Council International.</p>\n\n    <p>For more than a decade, the Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport has been the world&#39;s busiest airport, and is expected to retain its No. 1 spot in 2012. From January to November in 2012, the airport handled the enplanement and deplanement of more than 88 million passengers, an increase of 3.3 percent over 2011. In spite of its tremendous passenger volume, Atlanta&#39;s airport earns high marks in on-time measurements. The airport infrequently experiences flight cancellations, at a rate of a little more than half of one percent.</p>\n\n    <p>&#8220;We urge travelers not to automatically avoid busy airports,&#8221; says Julia Graft, FF PR manager. &#8220;Airports like Atlanta&#39;s can sometimes offer more available routes and capacity and may be more efficient than smaller, regional airports.&#8221;</p>\n\n    <p>China&#39;s Beijing Capital International Airport is a distant second to Atlanta with 75 million passengers from January to November, 2012. It will likely retain its No. 2 ranking in 2012, experiencing a 4.3 percent increase in passenger traffic. A bustling hub for Air China, the airport earned high marks in customer service in 2011, placing third in the Airports Council International&#39;s Airport Service Quality Awards.</p>\n\n    <p>London&#39;s Heathrow Airport and Chicago&#39;s O&#39;Hare International Airport will likely end 2012 at third and fourth places, respectively. Heathrow handled more than 64 million passengers during the first 11 months of 2012. Its entire network of six London-area airports is consistently ranked as the busiest airport system in the world. O&#39;Hare&#39;s traffic is relatively close to Heathrow&#39;s, with 62 million passengers during the 11-month period. O&#39;Hare&#39;s growth for the year was small, at just under one percent.</p>\n\n    <p>Tokyo international airport in Japan experienced a stellar 8.1 percent increase in the first 11 months of 2012, with nearly 62 million passengers in the first 11 months of 2012. The airport has ranked fifth on the list each year since 2009.</p>\n\n    <p>The only airport new to the preliminary Top 10 list is Indonesia&#39;s Soekarno-Hatta International Airport at No. 10. &quot;The airport has steadily risen in the rankings over the past few years, placing 12th in 2011 and 16th in 2010,&quot; notes Graft. &quot;Its 15.6 percent increase in passenger traffic is significant and makes it an airport to watch in the coming months.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>Here are the preliminary rankings for the 10 busiest airports in the world for January to November, 2012:&#160;<br />\n    10. Indonesia Soekarno-Hatta International Airport &ndash; 52.6 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    9. Frankfurt Airport, Germany &ndash; 53.5 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    8. Dallas-Fort Worth International, U.S. - 53.7 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    7. Charles de Gaulle Airport, Paris, France &ndash; 56.9 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    6. Los Angeles International, U.S. - 58.4 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    5. Tokyo International, Japan &ndash; 61.9 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    4. Chicago O&#39;Hare International, U.S. &ndash; 62.1 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    3. London Heathrow, United Kingdom &ndash; 64.4 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    2. Beijing Capital International, China &ndash; 75.3 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    1. Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International, U.S. - 88.0 million passengers&#160;<br />\n    &#160;</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(10, ' FlyFirst Announces Top 10 Best Seats in First Class Cabin, Cheap Tickets, Airline business cheap tickets, Airlines discounted, cheap airfares, last minute business class fares, discounted airlines deals', 'Cheap Tickets, Airline business cheap tickets, Airlines discounted, cheap airfares, last minute business class fares, discounted airlines deals', ' FlyFirst Announces Top 10 Best Seats in First Class Cabin', 'First-Class-Cheap-Dsicount', '2013-06-04 09:31:01', 'Today&#39;s competitive airlines build their reputations on meeting first class passenger expectations of superior facilities, the finest amenities and five-star service. &ldquo;Elaborate first class airport lounges only go so far, however, in keeping the first class passenger satisfied,&rdquo; says&#160;FlyFirst&#160;PR Manager Julia Graft. &ldquo;The in-flight first class seat is just as critical in earning the loyalty of well-heeled travelers.&rdquo;\n', '<p>Today&#39;s competitive airlines build their reputations on meeting first class passenger expectations of superior facilities, the finest amenities and five-star service. &#8220;Elaborate first class airport lounges only go so far, however, in keeping the first class passenger satisfied,&#8221; says&#160;FlyFirst&#160;PR Manager Julia Graft. &#8220;The in-flight first class seat is just as critical in earning the loyalty of well-heeled travelers.&#8221;</p>\n\n    <p>To help travelers get the most out of their first class fares, the business and first class travel experts at FlyFirst (FF) recently compiled a list of the Top 10 Best First Class Seats.</p>\n\n    <p>Always at top-of-mind for its elegant service, Qatar Airways does not disappoint with its first class seating. The service is exquisite, including a 10-course meal with caviar and free-flowing champagne. The seats are equally impressive with generous storage space, a personal television and seats that extend to full-flat beds for long overnight flights.</p>\n\n    <p>U.S.-based carriers infrequently attain a spot on these first class lists, but FF likes American Airlines relatively new swivel seats. The first in the industry to offer swivel seating, American Airlines&#39; seats recline to a 6&#39;6&#8221; full-flat bed, and the seat&#39;s two drop-down arm rests provide extra space. The seats operate electronic reclining and lumbar support for additional on-board comfort.</p>\n\n    <p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">Lufthansa&#39;s First Class cabins include spacious leather seats that convert to full-flat beds. The airline&#39;s 747 aircraft offer first class passengers both a seat that converts to the bed and a chair so that travelers can visit with one another or just spread out. Cabin humidifiers are a nice touch, as are the fine dining options.</span></p>\n\n    <p>First class passengers have more room to spread out and enjoy a little privacy aboard Cathay Pacific. The airline only installs six to nine first class seats on any airplane, in a 1x1x1 configuration. &#8220;That limited seating translates into more personal space and less aisle traffic,&#8221; Graft says. The airline, known for its first class service, offers all the usual first class amenities as well, including a personal television monitor, storage space and plenty of champagne.</p>\n\n    <p>Aboard Emirates&#39; Airbus 380, first class seats are actually private suites with full-flat beds and turn-down service. The on-board showers nicely complement other amenities and in-flight entertainment system that always receives top marks from passengers.</p>\n\n    <p>FF enjoys Etihad&#39;s push-button control seats that lie fully flat at an impressive 6&#39;8&#8221; and Malaysia Air&#39;s comfortable seats/beds, top-notch linens, toiletries and soft pajamas. Rounding out the list of the top 10 first class seats are <a href="http://www.iflyfirstclass.com/" target="_blank" title="cheap business class with Singapore air">Singapore Airlines</a>, Qantas, and Jet Airways. Singapore Airlines&#39; Airbus 380 first class seats are leather and span 35 inches across. Situated in individual pods, the seats offer privacy and large television monitors. Qantas&#39; provides very large seats with plenty of privacy, ample storage and a plush sheepskin underpaid for sleeping. Jet Airways&#39; first class seating includes excellent in-flight entertainment, comfortable flat beds and sliding privacy screens.</p>\n\n    <p>For information about other first class seating options, contact the business and first class travel experts at FF by calling 888-347-7817&#160;</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11, 'Cheap Last Minute Business Class Ticket, Cheap First Class Fare, Discounted Airline Flights. ', 'Cheap Business and First Class fares, last minute business class, cheap airline , last minute business class cheap', 'FlyFirst Announces Up to 65% Off All Summer International Business Flights', 'Business-International-Flights', '2013-06-09 18:56:09', 'Today, business class and first-class travel leader FlyFirst announced summer blockbuster discounts of up to 60 percent off all international business flights on major airlines\n', '<p><strong>FlyFirst Announces Up to 65% Off All Summer International Business Flights</strong></p>\n\n    <p>Today, business class and first-class travel leader FlyFirst announced summer blockbuster discounts of up to 60 percent off all international business flights on major airlines</p>\n\n    <p>The dramatically discounted rates are valid on a variety of tickets, including last minute fares on all major airlines and first class flights to South America aboard American Airlines. &#8220;We work diligently to negotiate the very best rates possible on first-class and business class flights,&quot; says Julia Graft, PR manager for FlyFirst, &quot;and we are proud to offer these outstanding fares to our treasured customers.&#8221;</p>\n\n    <p>The special summer savings are valid on the following travel options:&#160;<br />\n    - Last minute fares on all major airlines&#160;<br />\n    - Business and first class fares on American Airlines routes to South America&#160;<br />\n    - Business and first class tickets to Asia on all major airlines&#160;<br />\n    -Business Class and First Class&#160;on all major Airlines</p>\n\n    <p>At regular fares, a first class passenger on a major U.S. airline could expect to pay $7,000 to $14,000 on a first class flight from Los Angeles International Airport to Rome&#39;s Fiumicino Airport in July. These new deep discounts offered at FlyFirstoffer a remarkable cost savings, slashing some fares by as much as 60 percent as well as for Business Class flights.</p>\n\n    <p>The discounted rates are ideal for luxury vacation travelers and busy executives traveling for professional purposes. &#8220;Business class and first-class travel is now well within reach for most professional and personal budgets,&#8221; says Graft. &quot;Summer is a great time to experiment with luxury travel anyway, since business class and first-class tickets are less in demand. Add our steep discounts into the mix, and we know we can offer an unbelievable savings package for our customers.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>Summer discounted flights must be booked by May. 25, 2013, and are available only for groups of up to three people. Summer discounts apply only to air fares, not to any hotel or car costs.</p>\n\n    <p>To access these unprecedented business class and first-class international air fares, contact one of FlyFirst&#160;knowledgeable travel specialists today at (888) FIRST 17 or (888) 347-7817, or contact us online @ www.FlyFirst.com</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
