(29, 'Discount Business Class to Europe, Cheap First Class to Spain, Last Minuet Flights', 'Best Deals Business Class, Cheap First Class Air, Last Minute Deals to Spain, save on business class', 'Discounted Business Class to Spain, Save Thousands on First Class, Call Us Now or Send Your Request ', 'Cheap-Business-Class-Discount-To-Europe', '2013-06-30 17:18:14', 'FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights to Europe, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares to Spain. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets.Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.\n', '<p><strong>Cheap Business &amp; First Class Flights to Spain.&#160; Save Thousands on Last Minute Business Class Tickets. Affordable Price for Business Class Seats. Call Us Now to Book &amp; Save up to 70%</strong></p>\n\n    <h2>Palaces, Paella and Mountain Peaks&#160;</h2>\n\n    <div>Warm people and an even-warmer climate beckons you to the lovely country of Spain. With ravishing cathedrals and palaces, there are plenty of cultural sites to explore in Spain&#39;s many cities.</div>\n\n    <div>&#160;</div>\n\n    <div>Famed Spanish artist Gaudi grandly designed nine of Barcelona&#39;s magnificent structures, such as the Sagrada Familia, and should not be missed. Other fascinating sites in Barcelona include the Picasso Museum and the Catalan Gothic-styled Barcelona Cathedral.</div>\n\n    <div>&#160;</div>\n\n    <div>In Madrid, visitors delight in the Plaza de Cibeles and the 18th century Royal Palace, the Spanish Royal Family&#39;s official residence. The palace holds 3,418 rooms, some of which are open to the public.</div>\n\n    <div>&#160;</div>\n\n    <div>The bustling coastal city of Valencia is the home of delectable paella and a cosmopolitan art scene. Revel in the artistry of the beautiful 15th century Silk Exchange building, then head to the city&#39;s most iconic landmarks of Valencia Cathedral and its Miguelete Tower.</div>\n\n    <div>&#160;</div>\n\n    <div>Dozens of other notable structures are spread throughout Spain, including the prehistoric Altamira Cave paintings in Cantabria, the ancient Roman Aqueduct of Segovia and Granada&#39;s grand Alhambra. The massive Alhambra holds a 9th century citadel, Muslim palaces constructed in the 14th century and a 16th century palace built for Charles V.</div>\n\n    <div>&#160;</div>\n\n    <div>Spain offers bountiful recreation at its many mountains, lakes and beaches. Burn off some of those late-night tapas calories by hiking or snowshoeing in the Pyrenees&#39; Sant Maurici National Park, or kayaking near the warm beaches of San Sebasti&aacute;n.</div>\n\n    <div>&#160;</div>\n\n    <h2>Sumptuous Seating to Spain</h2>\n\n    <div>Pamper yourself with the&#160;<strong>luxury</strong>&#160;you deserve by selecting first or business class flights to Spain with help from FlyFirst.com. As a premium passenger, you&#39;ll access exclusive airport lounges full of appealing services and high-end amenities. Expedited boarding and customs queues are frequently given to premium travelers, making your boarding and disembarking a pleasant, quick experience. On your flight, the pampering continues with five-star cuisine, over-sized leather seats, ample work spaces, privacy screens and bed turn-down service. You&#39;ll land in Spain rested and keen to explore.</div>\n\n    <div>&#160;</div>\n\n    <h2>Industry-leading FlyFirst.com Services</h2>\n\n    <div>Our knowledgeable travel professionals find the very best deals available on premium flights to Spain and offer you superior service and a variety of travel options. One-way trips, multi-city destinations and last minute seats on&#160;<strong>cheap first and cheap business class flights</strong>&#160;all receive our outstanding discounts of up to 70 percent. To secure your exceptional discounts on first class fares and&#160;<strong>business class flights</strong>, call us today so that you can be on your way to sunny Spain in no time.</div>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(30, 'Business Class Cheap, Last Minute First Class Fare, Discounted Business Class Fare ', 'Cheap First Class Fare, Save on Business Class Tickets, Last Minute Business Class Flight', ' FlyFirst Announces This Summer''s Busiest Airports in The World. Cheap Business & First Class , Save Thousands. Call Us Now ', 'Cheap-Business-First-Class-to-Europe', '2013-06-30 17:48:29', 'More than five billion travelers take to the skies each year, with a good many of those passengers heading to airports around the world in the three-month summer season. To help its customers select the best airport for their upcoming summer vacations, FlyFirst, a leader in the first and business class travel industry, recently announced its projections for the summer&#39;s most active airports around the world.\n', '<p><strong>FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights to Asia, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares to Asia. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.</strong></p>\n\n    <p>More than five billion travelers take to the skies each year, with a good many of those passengers heading to airports around the world in the three-month summer season. To help its customers select the best airport for their upcoming summer vacations, FlyFirst, a leader in the first and business class travel industry, recently announced its projections for the summer&#39;s most active airports around the world.<br />\n    <br />\n    Topping the list as the busiest airport is Atlanta&#39;s Hartsfield-Jackson International Airport. &quot;For more than 12 years running, Atlanta has been the busiest airport in the world, and we expect it to remain the top airport throughout the summer,&quot; explains FlyFirst PR Manager Julia Graft. &quot;The airport is convenient to a variety of vacation spots on the country&#39;s East Coast and is a frequent transition point for U.S. travelers heading to Europe and the Middle East.&quot;<br />\n    <br />\n    Even though it handles a tremendous passenger volume, the Atlanta airport offers excellent on-time flight performance, with 82 percent of its arrivals and 84 percent of its departures adhering to schedule. Infrequent flight cancellations at Atlanta also help summer travelers keep on track.<br />\n    <br />\n    With good on-time statistics and many flight options, FlyFirst cautions travelers not to automatically avoid busy airports. &#8220;Busy airports like Atlanta usually offer greater route availability, larger capacity and swifter efficiency than their smaller regional counterparts,&#8221; Graft says.<br />\n    <br />\n    Throughout the summer, Beijing Capital International Airport in China should maintain its rank as the second busiest airport. &quot;Travel to China and the Far East is growing, Graft says, &quot;and FlyFirst expects its summertime travel statistics to remain consistently vigorous.&quot;<br />\n    <br />\n    London&#39;s system of six active airports actually makes it the world&#39;s busiest airport system, but its Heathrow Airport usually ranks at No. 3 in the list of busy international airports. Not only is London the most-visited city in the world, it offers a variety of convenient links to other vacation spots in Western Europe. Considering all of those factors, FlyFirst expects London&#39;s Heathrow Airport to maintain its spot in the top five busiest airports throughout the summer of 2013.&#160;<br />\n    <br />\n    In recent years, popular Tokyo International Airport and Chicago&#39;s O&#39;Hare International Airport round out the annual list of top five busiest airports in the world, and FlyFirst anticipates they will remain bustling sites throughout the summer. Beyond these top five, however, other airports may become equally busy as families head to favored theme parks, treasured beaches and locales that are more easily reached during warmer months.</p>\n\n    <p><strong>Cheap Business &amp; First Class Flights to Asia. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Last Minute Business Class Tickets. Affordable Price for Business Class Seats. Call Us Now to Book &amp; Save up to 70%</strong></p>\n\n    <p>Orlando International Airport, already a busy airport, experienced more than 10 percent growth in international travel in the first quarter of 2013. Near popular theme parks such as Walt Disney World, Universal Studios Orlando and SeaWorld, Orlando is convenient to other Florida vacation spots and is a popular summer airport.<br />\n    <br />\n    Palma de Mallorca Airport in Spain is one of the busiest airports in Europe during the summer. With dozens of resorts, countless beaches, abundant attractions and a vibrant Old Town, Palma de Mallorca is a cherished summer holiday spot for Europeans. Palma de Mallorca Airport also is one of the region&#39;s less expensive airports and offers convenient access to a number of European cities. The airport served more than 22 million people in 2012.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(31, 'cheap Business Class flights to Asia,discounted First Class fares,Best Business Class Deals', 'cheap Business Class flights to Asia,discounted First Class fares,Best Business Class Deals', 'FlyFirst announces top 5 First Class Lounges. Super Luxury Travel and Cheapest Business Class with FlyFirst. Call Us NOW', 'Discount-Business-Class-Deals-First-Class-Travel', '2013-06-30 18:05:00', 'FlyFirst, a leading luxury travel service, today announced its selection of the top five first class lounges in the world. The travel experts at FlyFirst drew on their vast knowledge of the world&#39;s leading luxury lounges\n', '<p>FlyFirst, a leading luxury travel service, today announced its selection of the top five first class lounges in the world. The travel experts at FlyFirst drew on their vast knowledge of the world&#39;s leading luxury lounges, feedback from clients and information from industry analysts to develop its list.</p>\n\n    <p><strong>FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights to Asia, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares to Asia. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.</strong></p>\n\n    <p>&quot;This compilation of the world&#39;s top first class lounges helps us to inform our clients as they are planning their international travels,&quot; says Julia Graft, PR manager of FlyFirst. &quot;Our service is dedicated in providing the largest discounts on luxury travel and the most available travel options, so the list helps our clients make more informed decisions on which lounges and airports offer the greater perks.&quot;<br />\n    <br />\n    Taking the No. 1 spot on the FlyFirst list is Qantas Airways&#39; lounge at the Sydney Airport. Sleek lines, gleaming surfaces, floor-to-ceiling windows and deluxe services are showcased in the flagship lounge. An enchanting living plant wall stretches 98 feet and brings life to the space envisioned by Australian designer Marc Newson. Travelers can luxuriate in the pampering services at the lounge&#39;s Payot Spa, dine on delectable meals or relax in the 20,000 square foot library. The Qantas Sydney lounge offers sumptuous service and a welcoming ambiance that hits just the right note for FlyFirst luxury travelers.<br />\n    <br />\n    &quot;In their quest to capture the luxury market, airlines are spending millions of dollars on on-board seating, contracting with world-renowned designers and chefs and creating over-the-top airport lounges,&quot; Graft notes. &quot;As a result, the airlines that reach the FlyFirst Top Five list are airlines, like Qantas and Lufthansa, that offer the most palatial lounges featuring the finest services and amenities.&quot;<br />\n    <br />\n    Lufthansa, at No. 2, offers so many exclusive services to its Frankfurt first class passengers that its lounge encompasses an entire two-story terminal. Valets greet passengers at the entry, where personal assistants take care of check-in, security and travel details. Once inside the lounge area, travelers relax in supple armchairs, rest on daybeds in quiet rooms and refresh in shower suites. Hot and cold buffets, a la carte meals, an extensive wine selection and cooling cocktails offer enough variety to appeal to every palate, and a fully equipped business center helps travelers conduct last-minute business necessities.</p>\n\n    <p><strong>Cheap Business &amp; First Class Flights to Asia. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Last Minute Business Class Tickets. Affordable Price for Business Class Seats. Call Us Now to Book &amp; Save up to 70%</strong></p>\n\n    <p>A perennial favorite, Qatar Airways is well-known for its refined first class service. Its flagship Doha Airport lounge is housed in its Premium Terminal, exclusive to first and business class travelers. Select passengers avail themselves of personal chauffeurs to the Premium Terminal, where they enjoy a serene ambiance, lounges filled with comfortable armchairs, fine dining, a global deli, cocktails, high tea, spa services and a host of other amenities created to pamper its discerning passengers.<br />\n    <br />\n    Refined elegance and gracious service are the hallmarks of Etihad and British Airways, at Nos. 4 and 5, respectively. At Abu Dhabi, Etihad&#39;s Diamond First Class passengers relish the flawless meals, roomy lounges and business services, while first class passengers at British Airways&#39; Concorde Room are greeted by large, glittering chandeliers and impeccable spa services.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(32, 'discount business class, cheap first class, save money discounts flights', 'cheap business class flight, discounted business cheap, last minute cheap tickets ', 'FlyFirst Class Announces top 5 Best Places to Visit in Europe. Save Thousands on Business & First Class', 'Cheap-Business-Class-First-Europe', '2013-06-30 18:23:24', 'With the summer travel season in full swing, FlyFirst announces its selection of the top five European towns to visit in 2013. Europe&#39;s many vibrant cities, appealing landmarks and exciting recreation spots make it difficult for travelers to decide where to spend their time. To help international globetrotters, the travel experts at&#160;FlyFirst&#160;reviewed European destinations, noting airport and flight access, public transportation availability and compelling attractions, recreation and historic sites.\n', '<p><strong>FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights to Europe, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares to Europe. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.</strong></p>\n\n    <p>With the summer travel season in full swing, FlyFirst announces its selection of the top five European towns to visit in 2013. Europe&#39;s many vibrant cities, appealing landmarks and exciting recreation spots make it difficult for travelers to decide where to spend their time. To help international globetrotters, the travel experts at&#160;<a href="http://flyfirst.com/" target="_blank" title="cheap business fare to Europe">FlyFirst</a>&#160;reviewed European destinations, noting airport and flight access, public transportation availability and compelling attractions, recreation and historic sites.</p>\n\n    <p>FlyFirst&#39; Top Five&#160;<a href="http://flyfirst.com/continent/Cheap-Business-Class-to-Europe" target="_blank" title="Cheap First Class Fare">European destinations</a>&#160;are world-class cities, each with its own trademark ambiance and rich cultural heritage. Beyond a wealth of historic sites, each Top Five city offers plenty of things to see and experience, whether travelers are there for two days, two weeks or two months.</p>\n\n    <p>Fresh off the heels of its successful 2012 Summer Olympic Games,&#160;<a href="http://flyfirst.com/city/Cheap-Business-Class-Tickets-to-London" target="_blank" title="cheap first class flight to London">London</a>&#160;is primed and ready to welcome the world. At the No. 1 spot, London offers the largest airport system in the world, with convenient public transportation links to the city core. With four World Heritage sites, including the Tower of London and Westminster Palace, history buffs delight in London&#39;s bountiful landmarks, castles and bridges. Visitors can explore art at Tate Modern, dine on ethnic dishes in the East End, savor a bird&#39;s eye view of the city aboard the London Eye and enjoy a rousing play in the West End.</p>\n\n    <p><strong>Cheap Business &amp; First Class Flights to Europe. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Last Minute Business Class Tickets. Affordable Price for Business Class Seats. Call Us Now to Book &amp; Save up to 70%</strong></p>\n\n    <p>Picturesque Frankfurt is No. 2 on the FlyFirst Class list, and offers its own entrancing views and activities.&#160;<a href="http://flyfirst.com/city/Cheap-First-Business-Class-Flight-to-Frankfurt" target="_blank" title="cheap last minute to Frankfurt">Frankfurt</a>boasts one of world&#39;s busiest airports and provides plenty of public transportation options. Historic architecture in the old Altstadt distict and the medieval R&ouml;mer provide a glimpse into Frankfurt&#39;s illustrious past, while dozens of museums encourage visitors to explore the region&#39;s progression of culture, art, industry and religion. Recreation is abundant in Frankfurt, particularly with its access to the 300-mile Main-Radweg bicycle path along the Main River.</p>\n\n    <p>The infamous City of Light is at No. 3, known for its well-planned streets, famed fashion houses, grand architecture and exquisite restaurants. More than 45 million tourists visit Paris each year, touring the Bastille, Versailles, Notre Dame Cathedral and the Tuileries Gardens. Perfumeries, couture apparel and top-of-the-line cosmetics create a shopper&#39;s paradise. The celebrated Louvre is just one of dozens of notable museums scattered throughout the city. Sporting and community events keep Paris aflutter in summer months, including national Bastille Day; outdoor movie festival, Cinema en Plein Air; French Tennis Open and Tour de France.</p>\n\n    <p>Gorgeous Zurich, at No. 4, is both charmingly historic and alluringly modern. It is home to one of the best airports in the world and offers one of Switzerland&#39;s largest passenger railway stations. Zurich is one of the continent&#39;s wealthiest cities with bountiful culture, from the Swiss National Musuem and Kunsthaus to the Zurich Museum of Art. Historic guild houses line Munsterhof Square, prehistoric settlements are revealed at Enge Alpenquai and glorious Fraumunster Church overlooks Lake Zurich. With Lake Zurich nearby and the Limmat River traversing the city, countless recreation opportunities keep thrill-seeking tourists satisfied.</p>\n\n    <p>Rome, The Eternal City, rounds out the FlyFirst Class list. Visitors relish the city&#39;s copious historic sites, including the Colosseum, Forum, Pantheon, Vatican City, St. Peter&#39;s Basilica and Trevi Fountain. Rome&#39;s city center is easily maneuvered on foot, but there is plenty of public transportation to aid travelers, from metro lines, buses and trams. Families particularly enjoy the city&#39;s Children&#39;s Museum, the Time Elevator, 3D Rewind and the zoo, Bioparco.</p>\n\n    <p>The travel specialists at&#160;<a href="http://www.flyfirst.com/" target="_blank" title="last minute cheap">FlyFirst</a>&#160;encourage travelers to visit one or more of these Top Five world-class cities for fascinating adventures and enriching experiences. For information about traveling in affordable luxury to these and dozens of other alluring European cities, call FlyFirst at (888)347-7817 or view information online at FlyFirst.com.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(33, 'Cheap Flights, business, first, discounted Flights Business Class, Last Minute ', 'best business class deals, cheap first class fares, last minute discounted airlines , save money on business', 'FlyFirst Class Announces Airline Traffic Statistic for The Beginning of Summer 2013. Cheap Business Class Flights and Discounted First Class Tickets to Europe. ', 'Business-Class-First-Class-Cheap', '2013-06-30 18:31:57', 'With May airline travel statistics trickling in, FlyFirst announced today that it expects the 2013 summer travel season to be very robust and to offer a number of record deals on first and business class flights.Although travel figures for May 2013 include a mixed bag of slight passenger increases counterbalanced by modest decreases, most industry analysts predicted that this year&#39;s summer months would be busy.&#160;FlyFirst, a leading service specializing in reduced-fare first and business class air travel, carefully watches airline and travel trends to better serve its premium clientele.\n', '<p>With May airline travel statistics trickling in, FlyFirst announced today that it expects the 2013 summer travel season to be very robust and to offer a number of record deals on first and business class flights.</p>\n\n    <p>Although travel figures for May 2013 include a mixed bag of slight passenger increases counterbalanced by modest decreases, most industry analysts predicted that this year&#39;s summer months would be busy.&#160;<a href="http://www.flyfirst.com/" target="_blank" title="cheap business class">FlyFirst</a>, a leading service specializing in reduced-fare first and business class air travel, carefully watches airline and travel trends to better serve its premium clientele.</p>\n\n    <p>&quot;Summer is traditionally the busiest leisure air travel season of the year,&quot; notes Julia Graft, PR manager for FlyFirst.com. &quot;Airlines were very busy in the summer of 2012, and we expect similar or higher numbers of passengers during the 2013 summer season.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>In spite of the high expectations for the coming summer travel season, May 2013 offered varied results for some of the world&#39;s largest airlines. Delta Airlines, Southwest and Lufthansa all showed a slight increase in the number of enplaned passengers in May 2013, with 14.26 million, 12.043 million and 9.377 million passengers, respectively. United Airlines and American Airlines both showed slight decreases in passengers in the same month.</p>\n\n    <p>Since the economic recovery began, each summer travel season has shown progress. In 2010, U.S. carriers reported serving 201.4 million passengers from June to August, and in 2011, 204.3 million international and domestic passengers were served on U.S. airlines. In 2012, that number reached 205.3 million passengers. The organization representing U.S.-based air carriers, Airlines for America, forecast that the country&#39;s airlines would serve nearly 209 million passengers in the summer of 2013.</p>\n\n    <p><strong>FlyFirst offers cheap Business Class flights to Europe, we specialize on last minute business class tickets, FlyFirst provides discounted First Class fares to Europe. Best Business Class Deals. Save Thousands on Business and First Class Tickets. Discount First &amp; Business Class Airline Tickets. First Class &amp; Business Class Travel Deals.</strong></p>\n\n    <p>July is traditionally the busiest month of the summer season, and FlyFirst expects that trend to continue for the summer of 2013. Summer air travel is lightest in the&#160;<a href="http://flyfirst.com/service/firstClass" target="_blank" title="Cheap First Class">first</a>&#160;two weeks in June and the last two weeks of August, when American schools are often in session.</p>\n\n    <p>&quot;Internationally, air passenger traffic has increased in recent years, growing by four percent in 2012,&quot; Graft says. &quot;In particular, we are seeing significant growth in international travel to the Middle East and Asia, where economies are expanding and the high-end of leisure travel is burgeoning.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>This increased summer demand actually offers good news for travelers&#39; pocketbooks. As international companies seek their own summer holidays, business travel throughout the world drops during the summer months. This decrease in demand for business and first class seats during the summer months leads to a significant drop in prices, opening the way for coach-fliers to afford luxury air travel.</p>\n\n    <p>&quot;At FlyFirst.com, we offer some of our very best first and&#160;<a href="http://flyfirst.com/service/businessClass" target="_blank" title="cheap business class">business class deals</a>&#160;to international and domestic destinations in the summertime,&quot; Graft says. &quot;More unfilled capacity in the luxury airplane sections makes first and business class travel more accessible to a greater variety of budgets.&quot;</p>\n\n    <p>Currently, FlyFirst is booking luxury travel throughout the summer to a variety of international and domestic destinations at up to 70 percent off published fares.</p>\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
