al way. A welcoming river promenade trails alongside the Rhine, perfect for strolling, jogging and skating. Just across from the peaceful promenade, the modern world flavors D&uuml;sseldorf&#39;s &quot;longest bar in the world,&quot; a series of more than 300 lively discos and bars.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAlstadt isn&#39;t the only historic district in town. The Kaiserswerth area holds the ruins of Castle Barbarossa and Florence Nightingale&#39;s old work site, the Deaconess&#39; Institute of Kaiserswerth. Visitors delight in the rococo ornamentation of 18th century Schloss Benrath, the grand dome of the Tonhalle Concert Hall and the city&#39;s plentiful museums and theaters.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor more modern experiences, visitors head to the Rhine Tower, Rheinturm, where a revolving restaurant and observation deck offer spectacular views. A lighted clock sculpture rests atop the tower, creating the world&#39;s largest digital clock. Shoppers enjoy the countless high-end jewelry and designer apparel shops in the K&ouml;nigsallee/King&#39;s Avenue area. Botanical gardens, bountiful parks, a bustling harbor and the ever-present Rhine River provide ample opportunities for visitors and locals to enjoy the cool climate and verdant landscape that is quintessentially D&uuml;sseldorf.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Create A Fairytale Trip to D&uuml;sseldorf</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Begin your journey to one of Germany&#39;s most beautiful cities in the magical splendor of first class seats and business class cabins. The deluxe service begins with elaborately designed and amenity-filled airport lounges, offering the ultimate in relaxation and refreshment for travelers. In the air, first and business class passengers are treated to delectable meals, abundant beverages, spacious seating, choice bedding and a host of other services to ensure a fairytale flight.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Industry-leading FlyFirst.com</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The opulent services of luxury travel are even more enjoyable with FlyFirst.com&#